        <num>CCRP 708</num>
        <heading>708.  Continuance and recess; definitions</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 708.  Continuance and recess; definitions
A continuance is the postponement of a scheduled trial or hearing, and shall not be granted after the trial or hearing has commenced.  A recess is a temporary adjournment of a trial or hearing that occurs after a trial or hearing has commenced.</p>
        </content>
